          keyIdea: 'Light is an electromagnetic wave travelling at 300,000 km/s. Its wavelength determines everything: colour, energy, and what it can do. Visible light is just a tiny slice of the full spectrum — the golden deer’s coat reflected wavelengths around 570–600 nm.',
