      offlineActivity: 'Build a pitcher plant trap model. Roll three paper cones with different rim widths (narrow, medium, wide). Coat the inner rims with: (A) nothing, (B) cooking oil, (C) oil plus a water spray. Drop 10 small beads (simulating insects) down each rim and record how many fall into the cone. Which combination captures the most? Compare your results with real pitcher plant anatomy — the oily, wet coating mimics the pitcher\'s waxy, nectar-covered peristome.',
